ergy parameters are critically discussed.\nPredictions for the position of the neutron drip line and the neutron skin\nthickness of selected nuclei are reported. They are only weakly affected by the\nchoice of effective mass values. Parts of the drip line can be sensitive to the\nSE parameters. The results underscore the role of Ktau and of precise\nastronomical input. Better constraints are possible with precise fits to\nnuclear energies and, in the future, more-precise input from astronomy.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Mon, 26 Oct 2020 05:46:40 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Thu, 29 Apr 2021 06:35:10 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-04-30"}
